rium in the\nsubsurface. The plausibility of primordial N2 as the primary source of Pluto's\nnitrogen (vs. NH3 or organic N) can be tested more rigorously using future\nconstraints on the 14N/15N ratio in N2 and the 36Ar/N2 ratio.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 May 2018 17:04:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-29"}
